cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with inferring a disentangled graphical description of objects from 2D images for volumetric reconstruction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generating volumes and disentangled graphical descriptions, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of a convolutional neural network suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves generating volumes and disentangled graphical descriptions from images and videos, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
